Name: ethanol production from maize | ethanol, without water, in 95% solution state, from fermentation | EN15804GD, U
Category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals
Description: The process described corresponds to the dry-milling corn-to-ethanol technology. The production of DDGS from stillage includes separation of draff, concentration, drying and granulation. DDGS are used as animal feed.
